snippet.textDisplay:
1. Dam mast qalandar ... as Tu chiz badi hai mast in "Mohra". (You know that)
2. Saanso ki maala ... AS IT IS in "Koyla". (Oops)
3. Kinna sohna tainu ... as Kitna pyara tujhe in "Raja Hindustani". (Really???)
4. Sanu ik pal chain ... as Mujhe Ek Pal Chain in "Judaai". (Nooooo wayyyy)
5. Dil pe zakhm khate hain ... as Dil ka kya kare sahib in "Jeet". (Now this is the limit yaar)
6. Heere ni Ranjha jogi ... as Fevikol se in "Dabangg 2". (This one is extraordinarily shameful as it is conversion of a Sufi beauty into hideous item number)
7. Nit khair manga sonya ... as Mera yaar dildaar in "Jaanwar". (Stopped counting now?)
8. Allaah hu ... as I love you in "Auzaar" ..... (Ya Allaah ... MADAD)
                           *** (NOT) THE END ***
Copies from legendary Sabri Bros.
1. Savere savere ... as Ye maana meri jaan in "Haste Zakhm". (Copied way back in 1970's, see, bollywoodiya mahachootiya are fast at copying ;-)   
2. Bhar do jholi ... AS IT IS in "Bajrangi Bhaijaan".
3. Mera Piya Ghar aaya ... AS IT IS in "Yaaraana".
4. Abke saal poonam me ... as Abki baar poonam me in "Janasheen". (Isse badhiya ghazal ki, isse ghatiya copy, KOI NAHI)
                           *** (STILL NOT) THE END ***
Copies from Reshma Bibi
1. Ankhian nu rehn de ... as Ankhiyo ko rehne de in "Bobby" (1973 movie ... Told you, Bollywood is not at all late when it comes to copying).
2. Ve main chori chori ... as Yaara sili sili in "Rudaali".
3. Lambi judaai ... AS IT IS in "Hero".
                           *** (STILL NOT) CONTENT??? ***
Copies from the uniquely talented Janaab Attaullah Khan, legendary Pakistani folk singer, lovingly called Lala Jee -
1. Balo batiyan Ve Maahi ... as "Mujhko Dafna Kar" in an album of Sonu Nigam Sahab 
2. Achha Sila Diya ... AS IT IS in "Bewafa Sanam" 
3. Ni oottaan wale ... as Ho dil tod ke in "Bewafa Sanam"
